I've played a lot of kirby games and a some 3d action games (platinum games) as well. Even then using morpho knights sword it took me a few attempts to beat the final fight in the colosseum. Gura actually did very well all things considered. 

I really like these sort of challenges so I decided to do this without abilities and without buying items or paying to redo a boss and it took me  around 5 hours. I know people are joking when they're comparing the game to elden ring, but without abilities/items/retries they genuinely become comparable. Since in the colosseum you get very limited healing items you have to beat most bosses without taking damage more than a couple times, because otherwise you won't have enough hp for the final boss. and without abilities a lot of the harder fights last at least a few minutes (over 10 minutes for the final one).

¬†@captainblue5096¬† I've played the arena with a handful of different abilities and from my experience while playing without abilities is definitely not the hardest way to play it isn't anywhere near the easiest either. Especially compared to morpho knights sword which not only does way more damage, but also heals which makes it incredibly broken for this. I'd even say that from my experience, meta knights sword as well as most level 3 abilities are better than no ability. The big difference is that without abilities bosses tend to take nearly twice as long. Also there's a few bosses in particular where no abilities is really hard because they don't give you a lot of chances to pick up the stars without taking damage. Also most bosses give you moments where you can attack without a risk even without abilities which makes a defensive strategy valid with most abilities. 

If you want a really hard challenge. Right now I'm trying the arena with level 1 sword (no buying items/restarting) and it's way harder than with no abilities. A lot of the fights take like 4-5 minutes to beat and to attack you have to be right next to them.
